properties.feesApplyText:
What will renting this property cost you?

As well as your regular rental payments, you may also be required to make the following permitted payments.

Prior to the start of the tenancy
  • Holding Deposit - 1 week's rent
  • Security Deposit - 5 week's rent

  • During the tenancy

    • Late rental payment interest charge - 3.10% of amount owed
    • Change of tenancy charge £50

    • If you require a key or key fob for the property to be replaced, the cost of the replacement key/fob will be passed on to you with an invoice to demonstrate proof of cost.

      If you request an early termination of your tenancy, outside of any break clause stated in your tenancy agreement, you may be required to make payment of rent until the tenancy is terminated and cover the loss incurred by your landlord. You will be provided with an invoice to demonstrate proof of the landlord's loss.

      Unless otherwise agreed in your tenancy agreement, you will also be responsible for paying for the following (if connected to the property):

    • Utilities - gas, electricity, water
    • Media - telephone, broadband, television packages (satellite/cable) and television licence
    • Council Tax

    How do we ensure our tenants are protected?

    We are a registered member of the Propertymark Client Money Protection Scheme, which is a client money protection scheme to ensure your money is handled within the correct manner. We are also members of The Property Ombudsman, which is a redress scheme for consumer complaints. You can find out more information on our website, or by contacting your local office.

properties.feesApplyText:
TENANCY FEES

Information and Terms for Tenants

Holding Deposit
In order to secure a property a holding deposit of a maximum of 1 week's rent is required. This will be deducted from the first month's rent. If you fail to occupy the property through no fault of your own, then the holding deposit is completely refundable. If your references are deemed to be unsuitable or you simply change your mind, then the holding deposit will be retained by Christopher Charles.

Tenancy Deposit
A deposit equivalent to 5 weeks rent must be paid in cleared funds prior to the commencement of any tenancy. If we manage the property, the deposit is held by Christopher Charles as stakeholders for the duration of the tenancy agreement and is held against rent arrears, damages/dilapidations to the property. Other wise if the property is non-managed the deposit is held by the landlord. At the end of the tenancy agreement the deposit is returnable subject to a final inspection and full inventory check.

Rent
One month's rent payable in advance, payable no later than 7 days prior to the move date

Method of payment for rent:
The rent should be paid by standing order and this should be set up prior to commencement of the tenancy. A lead tenant should be appointed and a standing order facility set up between that person and Christopher Charles/Landlord for the total amount of the rental on that property.

Permitted Payments

Rent
Rent must be paid on the due date, if not, interest will be charged at 3% above Bank of England's base rate on a daily basis.

Keys
Payment of £50 for the reasonably incurred costs for the loss of keys/security devices. Should the locks need to be changed then there will be additional costs.

During the Tenancy
During the tenancy the tenant must pay for the gas, electricity, water and council tax.

Varying of the Contract
If there is a change of tenant during the term of the agreement a charge of £50 per tenant will apply 

Early Termination
Should the tenant wish to leave their contract early, they shall be liable to the landlord's costs in re-letting the property.

Tenancy deposit protection Scheme
Where the deposit is held by Christopher Charles, the deposit is protected using   , which is government registered scheme. In case of dispute the matter will be referred to an independent adjudicator.

Client Money Protection:

Christopher Charles confirm that they have client money protection in place and this is with CMP Client Money Protect. Client's money is held by HSBC 789 High Rd, London N12 8JX.

Redress Scheme:

Christopher Charles is part of the TPOS (The Property Ombudsman Scheme) redress scheme which independently reviews complaints. For more information please visit their website

When taking a property the only charges you will be liable for are:

a) The Rent

b) A tenancy deposit equivalent to 5 weeks rent where the annual rent is less than £50,000 or 6 weeks where the annual rent is in excess of £50,000

c) A refundable holding deposit equivalent to one weeks rent to reserve the property.

d) Changes to the tenancy when requested by the tenant no more than £50 or reasonable costs incurred if higher

e) Payments associated with early termination of the tenancy when requested by the tenant.

f) Payments in relation to Utilities, TV License, Communication Services and Council Tax.

g) A default fee for late payment of rent and replacement of lost keys/security device, where required under the tenancy agreement.

Please Note: Costs and any default fees remain in place for all tenancies executed before 1st June 2019. This includes referencing fees of £100.00 per person; dilapidation deposit of 6 weeks rent; a Check-Out charge of between £140.00 & £190.00; any other fees or charges stipulated in the Tenancy Agreement.

properties.feesApplyText:
Letting Information
When renting a property, there are various costs that you will need to take into consideration when making an offer

Prior to your Tenancy:
- Advance Rent: As a minimum, the first months rent is payable before your tenancy commences, (may differ dependent on the terms of your tenancy).
- Tenancy Deposit: Equivalent of 5 weeks rent (if annual rent is less than £50,000) or 6 weeks rent (if annual rent is £50,000 or more), payable before your tenancy commences.

During your Tenancy:
- Late rental payment. Interest will be charged at 3% per annum over The Bank of England base rate.
- Lost keys or other security devices: The costs of replacing them plus if required, the costs of a locksmith, new lock and replacement keys for anyone requiring keys.

Other fees that may apply:
- Tenancy Swap: £50 (inc. VAT) plus any reasonable costs incurred if higher, will be payable by the tenant subject to the landlords consent and reference approval.
- Variation of Contract: £50 (inc. VAT) per variation will be payable by the tenant subject to the landlords consent.
- Early Termination of Tenancy: All landlords costs in re-letting the property plus all rent, council tax and utilities due under the tenancy until the start date of the replacement tenancy. The costs will be no more than the maximum amount of rent outstanding on the tenancy.

Additional Information
- Independent Redress: NowProperty is a member of The Property Ombudsman (TPO) scheme and subscribes to the TPO Code of Practice for Residential Lettings Agents.
- Client Money Protection: NowProperty is a member of the SafeAgent Money Protection Scheme, ensuring the security and protection of client funds.
